<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFE689637DCDA5A8B987FD11" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFE689637DCDA5A8BB5DFCC8" blockId="48.[151,1436,1546,2036]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1436,152,294]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE689627DCDA5A8BB63FB90" bold="true" box="[199,320,1933,1959]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
Kato’s remark that 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE689627F3BA5A8B8B2FB91" box="[561,657,1933,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Midoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE689627F3BA5A8B8B2FB91" box="[561,657,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Midoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE689627E74A5A8BE20FB91" box="[894,1027,1933,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE689627E74A5A8BE20FB91" box="[894,1027,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Daimachus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(not available for examination) is probably misleading— 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE689627CAEA591B809FBFA" box="[420,554,1972,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE689627CAEA591B809FBFA" box="[420,554,1972,1997]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Daimachus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently placed in the 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE689627E52A591BE8DFBF9" authority="(Oman et al. 1990)" baseAuthorityName="Oman" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[856,1198,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ulopinae">
Ulopinae (
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFE689627ED9A591BE87FBF9" author="Oman, P. W. &amp; Knight, W. J. &amp; Nielson, M. W." box="[979,1188,1972,1998]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref59081" refString="Oman, P. W., Knight, W. J., and Nielson, M. W. (1990) Leafhoppers (Cicadellidae): a Bibliography, Generic Check-list and Index to the World Literature 1956 - 1985. CAB International Institute of Entomology, Wallingford, Oxon, United Kingdom, iii + 368 pp." type="book" year="1990">
Oman 
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE68962792EA591BE7DFBFA" box="[1060,1118,1972,1997]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. While ulopines and ledrines share many characters (reduced leg spinulation, crown sometimes produced or flattened, texture of the dorsum sometimes punctate), they are clearly distinct from one another. Kato’s characters (ocelli position, metathoracic tibia) and illustration for 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE789637F66A29AB8EFFCEF" box="[620,716,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Midoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE789637F66A29AB8EFFCEF" box="[620,716,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Midoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest it is a ledrine, perhaps proximate to 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE7896379FFA29ABF5AFCEF" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1972" box="[1269,1401,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hangklipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE7896379FFA29ABF5AFCEF" box="[1269,1401,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Hangklipia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFE789637D9DA2C0BB54FCC9" authorityName="Kato" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,375,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parapetalocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFE789637D9DA2C0BB54FCC9" box="[151,375,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Parapetalocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFE789637DCDA329B987FD11" blockId="49.[151,1436,152,294]" box="[199,932,268,294]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
